    "body": "I did some debugging and the problem seems to be happening here: https://github.com/starship/starship/blob/master/src/modules/directory.rs#L108\n\nI added debug lines to get an excerpt of what each variables around that contains to better understand what was happening:\n\n~~~\n[DEBUG] - (starship::modules::directory): prefix: \"\"\n[DEBUG] - (starship::modules::directory): repo_root: \"/home/gabster\"\n[DEBUG] - (starship::modules::directory): contracted_path: \"gabster/Downloads\"\n[DEBUG] - (starship::modules::directory): repo_path_vec: [\"gabster\", \"Downloads\"]\n[DEBUG] - (starship::modules::directory): after_repo_root: \"/Downloads\"\n[DEBUG] - (starship::modules::directory): num_segments_after_root: 2\n[DEBUG] - (starship::modules::directory): before: \"~/Downloads\" ; root: \"gabster\"\n[DEBUG] - (starship::modules::directory): path_vec: [\"~/Downloads\", \"gabster\", \"/Downloads\"]\n~~~\n\nthe result of `contract_repo_path()` returns something with an extraneous directory element, the name of the home directory. the best result in the scenario where the home directory is the repo root would be to see `~` get colored as the repo root and not see the extra name of the home directory (here `gabster/`).\n\nwe'd also need to add another unit test for `contracted_repo_path()` to test the result of the function when the repository path is the home directory.\n\nhowever, that's as far as I was able to go since my level of comfort with Rust is really not great yet. If someone is able to take the information above and implement a fix from that it would be super helpful.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
